<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8206333>
    dc:description "Fig.1 Arthrolycosa wolterbeeki sp. nov., the oldest fossil spider (Arachnida: Araneae) from Germany, from the late Carboniferous of Piesberg near Osnabruck, Lower Saxony. a Part. b Counterpart. Scale bar equals 5 mm" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8206333/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8206335>
    dc:description "Fig. 2 Interpretative camera" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8206335/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8206337>
    dc:description "Fig. 3 Details of the specimen shown in Fig. 1. a Setose distal ends of walking legs I and II. b Setae adorning the pedipalp. c Putative spinneret show- ing evidence of segmentation (arrowed). Scale bars equal 1 mm" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8206337/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

